---
description: Railway deployment for FeedFoundry
globs: "**/Dockerfile,**/railway.json,infra/**"
alwaysApply: false
---

Deploy **two services** from this monorepo: `apps/api` (FastAPI) and `apps/worker` (Python worker). Share the same `DATABASE_URL` and storage credentials.

Set all secrets in Railway environment variables, not in code. Use distinct envs for development, staging, production.

Worker should scale horizontally only after queue semantics are safe (DB row locking or Redis migration).

Prefer health checks on `/v1/health` for the API service.

Review Railway MCP actions before applying; destructive operations are limited but changes affect production infrastructure.
